result.execSummary:
The defendant Ashley Marie Gary was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 3rd Degree Sexual Assault, a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: If probation becomes revoked, the defendant is to receive credit for 1 day served.

miscConds.notes:
-Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent including any counseling and/or treatment as recommended.
-No Contact with the victim.  Forms of no contact include: in person, in writing, by telephone, by e-mail, or by any other forms of electronic communication, or through a third party intending to circumvent the no contact provision.
-No unsupervised contact with any children under the age of 18 years.
-HIV & STD testing w/in 25 days
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.
-Defendant to register for the sex offender registry.

timeConds.notes: To commence within 60 days.  Court grants huber, out of county service and out of county travel.

records.addlTxt:
3:19 p.m.  Defendant present in court with Atty Barb Privat.  Lisa Vanden Branden for the State of Wisconsin.  Court recites agreement - defendant will plea to an amended count of 3rd Degree sexual assault in violation of 940.225(3) (a class G felony) with probation.  State concurs.  Atty Privat concurs.  Defendant concurs.

Court goes over plea questionnaire with the defendant.  Court goes over constitutional rights with the defendant - defendant waives these rights.  Court goes over the elements of each offense.  Court instructs defendant of the maximum penalty.  Court instructs defendant regarding deportation.  (If felony) Court instructs regarding felony prohibitions.

Defendant enters a plea of GUILTY.  Court finds the plea is made freely, voluntarily, intelligently and understandingly.  Court finds there is a factual basis to support the plea.  Court finds the defendant guilty on the amended count 1.  Court orders the judgment of conviction be entered here today.  ADA confirms compliance with victim witness rights.  Sentencing statement by ADA.  Sentencing argument by Atty Privat.  Statement by the defendant.

Court sentences the defendant to: 

-SWD, and places the defendant on probation for 5 years.

CONDITIONS:

-120 days county jail.  To commence within 60 days, with huber, out of county service and out of county travel.
-Court costs.
-Defendant is to abide by all rules and recommendations of the supervising agent including any counseling and/or treatment as recommended.
-No Contact with the victim.  Forms of no contact include: in person, in writing, by telephone, by e-mail, or by any other forms of electronic communication, or through a third party intending to circumvent the no contact provision.
-No unsupervised contact with any children under the age of 18 years.
-HIV & STD testing w/in 25 days
-Defendant is to submit a DNA Sample.
-Defendant to register for the sex offender registry.

Court has no objection to serving the probation out of state.
Court grants the defendant 1 day of credit if revoked.

Court adjourned at 3:35 p.m.
